## Error Analysis

The build fails with **"Installed (but unpackaged) file(s) found"** â€” six files were installed into the buildroot but not listed in `%files`:

| File | Issue |
|---|---|
| `/bin/awk` | Symlink to gawk â€” should be removed or excluded on usrmerged systems |
| `/bin/gawk` | Binary installed to legacy path â€” must be removed on modern SUSE |
| `/usr/bin/gawk` | Main binary â€” **missing from %files** |
| `/usr/bin/gawkbug` | Utility binary â€” **missing from %files** |
| `/usr/lib/debug/usr/bin/gawk.debug` | Debug info for gawk (auto-generated, won't appear once gawk is in %files) |
| `/usr/share/man/man1/pm-gawk.1.gz` | Man page â€” **missing from %files** |

The root cause: the `%files` section only contains language files (`%lang`) and two profile.d configs. The actual binaries and man pages are not listed. The previous attempt removed a conditional block for non-usrmerge systems, which was fine, but the core files still need to be added.

## Fix Required

**Add these lines to the `%files` section:**

```
/usr/bin/gawk
%attr(755) %{_bindir}/gawkbug
/usr/share/man/man1/pm-gawk.1.gz
```

- `/usr/bin/gawk` â€” use `%{_bindir}` macro (i.e., `%{ _bindir}/gawk`) for forward compatibility, or the literal path.
- `gawkbug` â€” also under `%{_bindir}`, mark executable with `%attr(755)` if it isn't already set by default.
- The man page goes under `%{_mandir}` (i.e., `%{_mandir}/man1/pm-gawk.1.gz`).

**Remove the unpackaged `/bin/` paths.** Since this is a usrmerged system, gawk's build must be installing symlinks into `/bin/`. Add these lines to **`%install`** (before `make install`) to prevent legacy path installation:

```
rm -f %{buildroot}/bin/gawk
rm -f %{buildroot}/bin/awk
```

These two files are installed by gawk's own `make install` and must be cleaned up â€” they will not be needed on a usrmerged system.
