--- OLLAMA ERROR ANALYSIS ---
## Error Analysis

The build failed at the **%check-files phase** with `Installed (but unpackaged) file(s) found:` â€” six files were installed into the build root during `%install` but none of them appear in your `%files` section:

| File | Location |
|---|---|
| `/bin/awk` | /bin/ |
| `/bin/gawk` | /bin/ |
| `/usr/bin/gawk` | /usr/bin/ |
| `/usr/bin/gawkbug` | /usr/bin/ |
| `/usr/lib/debug/usr/bin/gawk.debug` | debug info (auto-generated) |
| `/usr/share/man/man1/pm-gawk.1.gz` | man page |

The previous attempts failed because the conditional logic (`%if !0%{?usrmerged}`) and selective file lists did not cover all installed paths. The `%files` section must explicitly list **every** file or directory that ends up in the build root â€” RPM does not auto-inherit files from `/bin`, `/etc/profile.d/`, or `/usr/share/man`.

## Fix Required (no [DEEP_ANALYZE] needed)

In your spec's `%files` section, replace the current `gawk.lang`-based file list with an explicit listing that covers all installed paths:

```
%files -f %{name}.lang
%config(noreplace) %{_sysconfdir}/profile.d/gawk.csh
%config(noreplace) %{_sysconfdir}/profile.d/gawk.sh
%{_bindir}/*
%{_mandir}/man1/pm-gawk.1.gz*
```

Key points:

- **`%{_bindir}/*`** covers `/usr/bin/gawk`, `/usr/bin/gawkbug`. On non-usrmerged systems where `/bin/awk` and `/bin/gawk` are symlinks or copies, this also picks them up via the symlink target. If you still see `/bin/awk` unpackaged on a legacy system, add `%{_sbindir}/awk` as well â€” but in modern Factory (usrmerged) builds `%{_bindir}/*` is sufficient and preferred.
- **Remove** the old conditional block (`%if !0%{?usrmerged}` â€¦ `/bin/awk`) that was only conditionally listing files â€” it's fragile and incomplete.
- **`%{_mandir}/man1/pm-gawk.1.gz*`** is mandatory â€” man pages under `%_mandir` are NOT auto-handled by RPM; they must be listed explicitly.
- The `/usr/lib/debug/usr/bin/gawk.debug` file is the **auto-generated debuginfo** entry for `gawk`. It will appear automatically once `gawk` (or `%{_bindir}/*`) is in `%files` â€” do NOT add a `-debuginfo` subpackage section manually.

After applying this change, re-run the build with `pbuild`.
